","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William De Swaithing was born in 1428, in Cranworth, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Edmund De Swathing I, was 39 and his mother, Agnes De Fransham, was 31. He had at least 1 son with Jane Woodhour. He died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1428–":"1428–Surnud","1428–Male":"1428–Surnud","1408–1428":"1408–1428","1417–1480":"1417–1480","1390–Male":"1390–Surnud","1397–1418":"1397–1418","1397":"1397","1480":"1480","1408":"1408","before 1418":"enne 1418","1418":"1418","1428":"1428","1390":"1390","1417":"1417","Cranworth, Norfolk, England":"Cranworth, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cranworth, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Cranworth, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1428–":"1428–Kuollut","1428–Male":"1428–Kuollut","1408–1428":"1408–1428","1417–1480":"1417–1480","1390–Male":"1390–Kuollut","1397–1418":"1397–1418","1397":"1397","1480":"1480","1408":"1408","before 1418":"ennen vuotta 1418","1418":"1418","1428":"1428","1390":"1390","1417":"1417","Cranworth, Norfolk, England":"Cranworth, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cranworth, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Cranworth, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningas